HEADWORD: Triceps
<hw>Tri"ceps</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL., fr. L.
<ets>triceps</ets>, having three beads; <ets>tres</ets>,
<ets>tria</ets>, three + <ets>caput</ets> head: cf. F.
<ets>triceps</ets>. See <er>Three</er>, and <ets>Chief</ets>.]</ety>
<fld>(Anat.)</fld> <def>A muscle having three heads; specif., the great
extensor of the forearm, arising by three heads and inserted into the
olecranon at the elbow.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Trichiasis</ent>⟦br⟧
